When the same data exists in components, services, stores, and forms, your application eventually stops knowing which version is correct.

5 min read
Just now

--

Press enter or click to view image in full size

Duplicate State Starts Innocently
Imagine a Customer feature that loads a list of customers.
The feature store keeps the data:
@Injectable()
export class CustomerStore {
private readonly _customers = signal<Customer[]>([]);readonly customers = this._customers.asReadonly();
}
A component also creates a local copy:
export class CustomerPageComponent {
private readonly store = inject(CustomerStore);readonly customers = signal<Customer[]>([]);
constructor() {
this.customers.set(this.store.customers());
}
}
Everything appears to work.
Then the component filters the list.
Another component updates a customer.
The store receives fresh data from the API.
Suddenly, multiple versions of the same information exist.
Which one is correct?
